Honduras confirmed its first two cases, one from Spain and one from Switzerland.[459]
Indonesia confirmed seven more cases, bringing the total number to 34.[460] Its first death was also reported,[461][462] confirmed by the United Kingdom's Foreign and Commonwealth Office as a 53-year-old female British national.
Iran announced that there are now 9,000 infected, with 354 deaths. New infections were 958 with 63 additional deaths. Those recovered total 2,959.[463] Iran's first vice-president, Eshaq Jahangiri was reported infected.[464]
Ireland confirmed nine additional cases, bringing the total number to 43. The first death was also confirmed.[465]
Israel confirmed 97 cases.[466]
Italy announced 2,313 new cases and 196 new deaths. Total cases stood at 12,462, with deaths at 827.[467] It was also confirmed Juventus and Italian footballer Daniele Rugani had tested positive for coronavirus.[468]
