Ireland confirmed 40 new cases, the largest to date. 169 total confirmed cases and 2 deaths.[655] The government requested all pubs and bars to close permanently from midnight, in advance of the then-upcoming 17 March Saint Patricks Day public holiday.[656]
Italy confirmed 3,590 more cases, bringing the total number to 24,747. The country also recorded 368 new deaths, bringing the total number to 1,809.[657] This was the largest death rate in a day for a country since the pandemic started.[citation needed] In addition, Vittorio Gregotti, the Italian architect that designed the 1992 Barcelona Summer Olympics stadium died at 92.[658]
