Italy reported 4,207 new cases and 475 new deaths. The total number of cases reached 35,713 and the total death toll rose to 2,978.[754]
Kyrgyzstan reported its first cases, three people who had recently returned from a pilgrimage to Saudi Arabia.[755]
Malaysia confirmed 117 new cases, bringing the total number to 790.[756]
Mauritius announced its first three cases.[757]
Moldova confirmed its first death[758] and six new cases, bringing the total to 36.
Montserrat confirmed its first case, a person who visited the United Kingdom.[759]
New Caledonia confirmed its first two cases.[760]
New Zealand confirmed eight new cases, bringing the total to 20.[761]
Nicaragua confirmed its first case, imported from Panama.[762][763]
Palestine confirms 44 cases.[764][765][766]
Panama confirmed several new cases, bringing the total to 109.[767]
Singapore confirmed 47 new cases, bringing the total number to 313. This was the highest number of new cases in the country in a single day so far.[768]
Slovakia confirmed its first death.[769]
South Korea confirmed 93 new cases and three new deaths, bringing the total to 8,413 and 84 respectively.[770]
Thailand confirmed 35 new cases, bringing the total to 212.[771]
The United Kingdom confirmed 676 new cases, taking it to a total of 2,626.[772] 32 additional deaths were announced, taking the total to 104.[773]
The United States confirmed 2,601 more cases, bringing the total number to 8,736. 37 more deaths were reported, bringing the total number to 149.[774]
Vietnam confirmed ten more cases, bringing the total number to 76.[775][776][777]
Zambia reported its first two cases.[778]
19 March
WHO Situation Report 59:[779]

Angola confirmed its first case, a Chinese businessman.[780]
The Canadian province of Ontario has reported a new record high of 43 new cases.[781] [782]
The Canadian province of Quebec has reported 27 new cases.[783]
Chad confirmed its first case, a Moroccan national who had travelled to the country from Cameroon.[784]
China reported no new cases of local infections but confirmed 34 new cases from overseas arrivals.[785]
Fiji confirmed its first case, a 27-year old flight attendant.[786][787]
Guatemala confirmed one additional case, raising the total to 9.[788]
Haiti reported its first two cases.[789]
Ireland confirmed 191 new cases, the largest to date with more than two and a half times the confirmed cases of 18 March, and a third death, bringing the total number of cases to 557.[790] Approximately 7,000 tests have been administered to date and the Minister for Health, Simon Harris, believes there will be 15,000 tests given a day starting within the next few days.[791]
Isle of Man confirmed its first case, a person who recently returned from Spain.[792]
Italy's number of cases rose to 41,035 from a previous 35,713, up by 5,322, a faster rate of growth than the past three days. They also overtook China as the country with the most deaths, registering 3,405 dead, a rise of 427 from the day before.[793]
Malaysia confirmed 110 new cases, bringing the total number to 900.[794]
New Zealand confirmed eight new cases, bringing the total to 28.[795][796]
Niger confirmed its first case, a local 36-year-old man who travelled a lot to Togo, Ghana, Ivory Coast and Burkina Faso due to work.[797]
Ibrahim Milhem confirmed three new cases bringing the total to 47. He said in the daily briefing that two cases were students returning home from France and quarantined before being in contact with anyone. The third is for a person from Nablus previously suspected of having the disease and was kept in home quarantine.[798]
Palestine confirms three new cases, bringing the total to 47.[798]
Panama reported several new cases, bringing the total number to 137.[799]
Pakistan confirmed 70 additional cases.[800]
Russia confirmed its first death.[801]
Singapore confirmed 32 new cases, bringing the total number to 345.[802]
South Korea confirmed 152 new cases and seven new deaths, bringing the total to 8,565 and 91 respectively.[803]
Spain reported a large increase in cases, with 17,147 cases and 767 deaths.[804]
Thailand confirmed 60 new cases, bringing the total to 272.[805]
The United Kingdom's total of diagnosed cases rose to 3,229, an increase of 603, with the death toll rising to 144.[806]
The United States confirmed 4,397 more cases, bringing the total number to 13,133. 46 more deaths were reported, bringing the total number to 195.[807] The Denver Nuggets, Los Angeles Lakers, Philadelphia 76ers, and the Boston Celtics all reported that some of their players had tested positive for the virus. The players had not been named.[808]
Vietnam confirmed nine more cases, bringing the total number to 85.[809]
